System Logs: OS-level events and operations (e.g., reboots, services)
â€¢ Windows Event Logs	Captures system, application, and security events on Windows.
â€¢ Sysmon Logs	Detailed Windows system activity logs (part of Sysinternals Suite).
â€¢ Linux/Unix Syslogs	General logging system for Unix/Linux (e.g., boot, cron, auth).

Network Logs: Tracks network traffic and communication-related activities.
â€¢ Firewall Logs: Shows allowed/blocked traffic and rules matched.
â€¢ Proxy Logs: Records requests going through web proxies.
â€¢ DNS Logs: Logs DNS queries and responses.

Application Logs: Logs generated by software applications and services.
â€¢ Database Logs	Monitors DB queries, errors, and transactions.
â€¢ Web/HTTP Logs	Tracks HTTP requests/responses from web servers.
â€¢ App Logs	Logs specific to applications (e.g., Java, .NET apps).

Security Logs: Focus on threats, attacks, and auth-related events.
â€¢ Authentication Logs	Logs login attempts, password failures, etc.
â€¢ IDS/IPS Logs	Logs intrusion detection/prevention alerts.
â€¢ Endpoint Sec Logs	Antivirus/EDR alerts, quarantines, detections.

Cloud Logs: Logs from cloud infrastructure and platforms.
â€¢ AWS CloudTrail Logs	Track AWS API calls and activity.
â€¢ Azure Logs	Logs from Azure activity and resources.

Audit Logs: Record of user actions or system changes for accountability.
â€¢ Audit Trail Logs	Tracks who did what and when for compliance.


